blocks.text: Barn along the Marietta Pike.

Nov. 5-Richard Nixon is elected President of the U. S. in close contest over Democrat Hubert Humphrey. Issues centered on the unpopular Vietnam war, the breakdown of law and order, the Negro and poverty programs. Both Houses of Congress will be Democratic. The nationally used Nixon slogan, shown on the billboard, was devised by John Connolly through his advertising agency which was the official agency for the Republican Party.

blocks.text: Lobster fishing is the chief occupation on Orr's Island. Boats, traps and fishermen can be seen at every cove..

The fisherman shown above with his young son and daughter has been lobster trapping since dawn. He brings in about 100 pounds of live lobsters for which he is paid sixty cents a pound, or about $60 for his morning's work. The live lobsters are then marketed to us for one dollar a pound, which is a low off-season price.
